This is a sample file, demonstrating the use of `checklist.js`, a bit of javascript that enables persistent checklists for assigned documents on Carnap. 

Note that the checklists will only be persistent when this document is made into an actual assignment.

For more details, see <https://github.com/dsanson/carnap-javascript>.

Here is a checklist:

<ul class="task-list">
<li><input type="checkbox" value="syllabus" disabled="" />
Read the syllabus</li>
<li><input type="checkbox" value="quiz 1" disabled="" />
Complete the syllabus quiz</li>
<li><input type="checkbox" value="sign up" disabled="" />
Create an account on Carnap.io</li>
</ul>

Here is the same checklist. These two checklists should stay synchronized (but I'm not sure this works quite right yet):

<ul class="task-list">
<li><input type="checkbox" value="syllabus" disabled="" />
Read the syllabus</li>
<li><input type="checkbox" value="quiz 1" disabled="" />
Complete the syllabus quiz</li>
<li><input type="checkbox" value="sign up" disabled="" />
Create an account on Carnap.io</li>
</ul>

Here is a checklist without `values`. This should cause the script to break:

-   [ ] item 1
-   [ ] item 2
-   [ ] item 3
